  "prompt": "When will I start the preparation of ilts?",
  "response": "The timing for starting your preparation for the IELTS (International English Language Testing System) depends on several factors, including your current level of English proficiency, your target score, and how much time you can dedicate to studying each week. Here are some steps to help you decide when to start:\n\n1. **Assess Your Current Level**: Take a practice test to determine your current proficiency level. This will give you a better idea of how much preparation you might need.\n\n2. **Set a Target Score**: Define what score you need for your goals (e.g., university admission, visa application). This will help you determine how much work you need to put in.\n\n3. **Determine Your Timeline**: Consider when you need to take the IELTS exam. Ideally, you should start preparing at least 2-3 months in advance, but if you\u2019re starting from a lower proficiency level, you may need more time.\n\n4. **Create a Study Plan**: Once you've assessed your level and set a timeline, create a study plan that includes areas such as reading, writing, listening, and speaking.\n\n5. **Monitor Your Progress**: As you prepare, regularly take practice tests to track your improvement and adjust your study plan as needed.\n\nIf you provide more details about your current situation, I can give more tailored advice!",
